annotationA: Monensin sensitivity 1 (Mon1) forms a complex with Ccz1 and acts as an exchange factor of the small G-protein Rab7. Mon1 activates and recruits Rab7 to the maturing endosome, where Rab7 organizes the fusion of the matured endosome with the lysosome. Mon1/Ccz1 complex loss of function results in Rab7 phenotypes
annotationB: Rab proteins geranylgeranyltransferase component A; Binds unprenylated Rab proteins, presents it to the catalytic component B, and remains bound to it after the geranylgeranyl transfer reaction. The component A is thought to be regenerated by transferring its prenylated Rab to a protein acceptor (By similarity)
